All four files are written and verified. Here's what was built:

---

**`public/meeting-notes.js`** (18KB)
- Auto-saves every field to Supabase on change (600ms debounce)
- Per-field `saved ✓` / `saving…` / `queued (offline)` indicators
- Offline queue in localStorage — flushes automatically when reconnected
- Completeness score tracks 12 core fields, updates live
- Unlocks tracker shows which downstream documents are ready (letter at 3, buyer targeting at 5, proposal at 6, full pipeline at 10)
- Loads prior saved data on page open and repopulates the form

**`templates/meeting-page-v2.html`** (25KB) — Jinja2 template
- Three tabs: Pre / During / Post — sticky navigation, mobile-responsive
- PRE: agenda, objectives, questions, talking points, danger zones, what we bring, success criteria, both next-steps branches, buyer table
- DURING: owner profile dropdowns, emotional temperature slider, revenue mix (4 fields), margin grid (gross/EBITDA/SDE), key employees table with add-row, deal breakers checklist, next steps checklist, verbatim quotes + story elements
- POST: completeness bar, unlocks tracker, auto-generated summary, action items panel, pre-filled follow-up email link

**`lib/meeting_engine_v2.py`** (20KB) — Python engine
- `MeetingEngineV2(supabase_client).render(company_id, meeting_date, meeting_type)`
- Three meeting types with distinct question sets: `discovery`, `financial_review`, `engagement`
- Fetches company, buyers, and prior meeting notes from Supabase — gracefully stubs if client is None
- Building hook uses prior `story_elements` if they exist from a previous session

**`public/meeting-aquascience-v2.html`** (35KB) — rendered proof
- All AquaScience content from the v1 page preserved and upgraded
- Meeting ID: `aquascience_2026-03-29_discovery` — this is what all Supabase writes will key against
- Live at the same `/meeting-aquascience-v2.html` path once deployed

One thing needed before the form writes actually land: the `meeting_notes` table needs a unique constraint on `(meeting_id, field_name)` for the upsert merge to work. Run this in Supabase SQL editor:

```sql
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS meeting_notes (
  id uuid DEFAULT gen_random_uuid() PRIMARY KEY,
  meeting_id text NOT NULL,
  field_name text NOT NULL,
  field_value text,
  captured_at timestamptz DEFAULT now(),
  UNIQUE(meeting_id, field_name)
);
```
